      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Those Who Wish Me Dead",
      "note": "with Bill Simmons",
      "guest": "Bill Simmons on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Those Who Wish Me Dead",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "Angelina Jolie smokejumper thriller from Taylor Sheridan, with Jon Bernthal, Nicholas Hoult, and Aidan Gillen as a very game Littlefinger. Plot holes and all, all three of them liked it, mostly for Gillen and Bernthal, despite Jolie, whose fame Bill argues has made her impossible to disappear into a part like this."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The Woman in the Window",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "The Woman in the Window",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "Joe Wright directs Amy Adams, Gary Oldman, and Julianne Moore from a Tracy Letts script, adapting Dan Mallory's (writing as A.J. Finn) bestseller. Both hosts call it the worst of Wright's recent run: a Rear Window knockoff that leans on old noir clips to fill space its own story can't."
        }
      ]
    },
